Today is Valentine's Day, the past is always over-consumption by the business of the heavy color of the day, this time some dim. Many lovers are still separated, and this is just one day in a long separation. Because of the epidemic, Qiwei, who lives in Wuhan, and her boyfriend, Yang Yujin, also rarely see each other. They are sealed off in their parents'homes and only met at the end of last month to take a group of photos and wear them in the streets. We chose Valentine's Day, a sunny day, to launch this collection of photos.

···············

On January 25, the first day of the Lunar New Year, on the third day of the city closure in Wuhan, a friend of Qi Wei posted a message on the hour -- "for the first time, I heard the ringing of the bell in Wuhan on the upper floor of my home. " An epidemic made Wuhan quiet. In the past, in this noisy metropolis, where the sounds of people and cars were interlaced, the bell of the Old Bell Tower could be heard unless you were right next to it at the hour. She took out her cell phone and recorded the sound, which came from three kilometers away.

On January 28, Qi Wei and her boyfriend Yang Yujin went out together to "sweep the streets" . "Street sweeping" , that is, with the camera to measure the pace of the city. It was the first sunny day in half a month in Wuhan that Qi Wei remembered. After that, the sunny day lasted for two or three days, and then returned to overcast and rainy. In order to shoot a documentary, Yang Yujin has been going out on and off since then, while filming the documentary to continue recording the city's footage. These days, with the change of diagnostic criteria, Wuhan new crown number of confirmed outbreaks again, February 12 at 0:00-24:00, Wuhan, 13,436 new cases of coronary pneumonia. The severity of the outbreak has increased, and photographers are staying at home, taking pictures and sliding them around the city along the river in a unique way.

January 31 was one of the most tense and grim days in the memory of the Internet, in front of the hospital, but for some residents of the city, it was the best day ever, sunny and long lasting.

This is Simeitang Park, which is surrounded by several communities and used to be very lively. She recorded a pop song still playing loudly in the park, "missing is a disease. ". When it came to the next Sammi Cheng Song, worth it, the old man at the foot of the pier was on the rise.

The girl standing in the window on the third floor is leaning out of the window, holding a pair of binoculars. She laughed out loud when she found herself in other people's cameras.

It was Sun yat-sen Avenue in Hankou, and the weather was fine, and some people came out carrying benches and wearing masks, "crunching" . Wuhan people said the "Grand Grand" , similar to Chengdu and Chongqing dialect in the "display of Dragon Gate Array" , idle, blah, blah, blah.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Jianghan Road Street, the old man moved a stool out in the sun. It's almost impossible to achieve in normal times -- Florida is part of an early settlement in Hankou, a patchwork of European architecture and local old town houses, a street that tourists fill up as soon as someone stops to take a picture, it'll cause a traffic jam.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
An Old lady was crossing the street diagonally, looking straight into the camera.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
We also see elderly people who refuse to wear masks. People use the Wuhan Dialect "Defy Zhou" (Defy Zhou) to describe their strong character, it is extremely difficult to persuade the middle-aged and old people who are not convinced by Zhou not to go out. They feel that their physical quality is very good. Qi Wei's aunt is still going to work every day, do some simple cleaning, disinfection work, aunt think, this work is very safe to do, disinfection process also put on the body.

This is Tongxingli. This is called "Lifen" in Wuhan typical residential form, many living facilities are public, residents live dense, mutual help, the alley is old, clean and bright. Lane on both sides of the two buildings between the pull a line, clothes hanging in the middle. You wear it on a weekday, you're taller, you brush the sheets over your face.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The ground floor of Lifen is now rented to many young people, and the owners live upstairs without interference. When young people moved in, they turned the old houses into creative shops and hung beautiful hand-painted signs. In the old days, the place was packed with tourists of the same age, trying on bracelets, drinking coffee, taking part in workshops and ticking off tourist tips.

Now, with the doors closed and the tide of young shopkeepers and tourists fading, the Lane seems to have been returned to its old resident, Foshan, for better or worse, clothes still need drying. Yang Jin felt that all the people in the alley had come out to dry their clothes.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Good weather, Yang Jin downstairs closed for a long time shop also quietly opened, a flower shop, a fruit shop. The proprietress sat in a sunlit spot in the shop, dozing. If someone comes, sell some. If no one comes, sell some.

It's a delivery man's plan. Yang Yujin followed him for a day, old plan talk about delivery when a girl, a person at home self isolation for more than 10 days, all access to external information from the network. She coughs, suspects she's sick, doesn't dare to check, cries at home all the time. The old plan to comfort her, the world is not so terrible. Back old plan to Yang Jin feeling, "if people stay in a place for a long time, it will be a problem, you do not come out to bask in the sun, you do not know you are still alive. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This is main street, Long Lake, Wuchang District. Two uncles sat playing chess while a child stood watching. Next door is a burial shop, surrounded by Chrysanthemum pots.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
This chrysanthemum is also a Spring Festival scene in Wuhan. On the eve of the Spring Festival every year, chrysanthemums appear in large numbers at the junctions of main roads, under flyovers and at crossroads. But as soon as you get close and act like you want to buy something, someone will pop up and say, "buy flowers? ".

What we see in Wuhan, the first generation of urban migrants to grow up in numbers that Shanghai and Beijing can not match, is that these workers are returned to their hometowns every Spring Festival. Statistics have been done, in recent years, each year will account for one-third of the total population to return home for the New Year, most of which is poured back to Hubei Province in other towns and villages. The old man in their family was buried in the mountain behind their house after their death. When they packed their bags for the Spring Festival, they would take a pot of chrysanthemums to put in front of their graves.

Even during the outbreak, even when it rained, the seemingly unguarded flowers stayed in their place. Just a day or two after the city was sealed off, Qi Wei passed by the Green Mountain area where many old people live. Every street was decorated with chrysanthemums. She wondered, "I don't know if anyone else would be out in the rain, or if the caretaker would just pop up. "

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
The ritualistic sense of death and burial is bound to fall at this time. Infectious Disease Present, the dead relatives are dealt with quickly, meet again, can only be a handful of ashes. And the people who do it for a living are still working. In a funeral supply store in an alley, the old man is making paper houses to burn to the ancestors. Three-story Mansion, just built the skeleton, put on the big wooden cabinet and color TV, paste the Chinese New Year "Fu" word.

The cigarettes on the old man's desk were a pack of Yellow Crane Tower, $40 a pack, but they were expensive, and the other two were cheap, a pack of white and a pack of Red Dragons. Chinese New Year, people pocket a packet of good cigarettes, a packet of cheap cigarettes, good cigarettes sent out, face. When no one else is around, you sneak back your cheap cigarettes. The photo only took one shot, just click, the old man swept to the corner of his head, angry, "shoot mosi shoot (shoot what shoot) . ". Scared him off.

From the alley has been to go out, went to the bridgehead, Wuhan every year from here to cross the river festival. From this famous viewing position, you can see landmarks such as the Yangtze River Bridge and the Kameyama TV tower.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
For Yang Yujin, the river has long lost its mystique. When the Yangtze River and the Han River River meet in Wuhan, the city is divided into three towns. The Yangtze River Bridge Connects Wuchang and Hanyang, and the Second Bridge Connects Wuchang and Hankou. Yang Yujin loves to walk, the Yangtze River Bridge, the Second Bridge, he walked countless times. "In Wuhan, no matter where you live, you cross the river almost every day. "

Out of the alley, down the river, you will be down a long row of stairs, people usually sit on top of the river view. The figure in the background is a young man, wearing a mask, sitting there for a long time.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
If you grew up in Wuhan, the light and color of the city in your memory might be half occupied by the light of the Yangtze River. The Yangtze River is much closer to the people of Wuhan than to many other cities that are also known as the water capital of Wuhan.

Every Wuhan Father, in his prime, may have swum across the Yangtze River and told the story over and over again as a legend in the eyes of his children. When she was in primary school, sitting on the edge of the river playing with sand, watching her father and his uncle go down the river together, she remembers the fear of losing her father in the line of sight. The more than 1,000-meter-wide river course to Tianxingzhou, my father ended up swimming about a quarter of the way.

In Wuhan, the river is everywhere, it belongs to the daily life of the citizens, it belongs to the old generation of wind and rain, thunder and lightning to walk along the river, and for those unruly young people, it also works hard to grow into their bodies.

Ziwei told me that people in Wuhan teach children to swim and don't go in the pool. Adults think it's better to throw their children into the river. She took a picture last summer of a five-or six-year-old boy crying in his underpants while his mother yelled and his grandmother worried. Mother said to and fro only one sentence, "cry Mosi cry, you go down you will swim. "

In the old man's mouth in Wuhan, a tender saying was repeated, feel the summer mosquito buzz, bite uncomfortable? All you have to do is soak your feet in the river and the mosquitoes won't bite.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In the days of the outbreak, many different photographers went to the riverbank to take pictures, because there were always people there. On the 28th, an old man caught a really big fish.

"really big AH, I think I eat alone, can eat for a week. " Yang jin-yu aftertaste up to marvel.

The old man was calm, could not see the expression under the mask, and threw the fish to the ground. And she shot a video on her phone, and she said, I don't know if he's happy, we're happy

The fish lay on the dry ground, stuck between two stones, and kept bouncing until they struggled to leave.

Turn around and head deep into Hubu Alley. Walk Down Qinglong Lane and you'll see Yellow Crane Tower in the distance. At night, the Yellow Crane Tower Lights Up, horribly red, "as if on fire. " The lights go on, and no one who lives here looks that way.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In her impression, since the Military Games began last October, yellow Crane Tower's like this. It glows at night. At 7:00 pm, the second hand just beat 00 minutes, the whole river, including Yellow Crane Tower, all landmarks, mountains, bridges lit up at the same time, red orange yellow green cyan-cyan-cyan-purple, constantly changing. These days, "Wuhan refueling" giant LED lights have been added up, more dazzling.

"refueling" just a few words, courage in the hearts of Wuhan People.
